None since single case report
Suggests most at risk:
People who are known to have previous psychiatric
illness;
• People with obsessive hypochondria or obsessive
compulsive disorders;
• Patients with recently diagnosed psychiatric
conditions;
• Patients with sleep and mood disorders without psychiatric
diagnosis (they go to the family doctor to be
prescribed sleeping pills);
• Patients with other chronic diseases;
Patients who live alone and who do not have a job;
• People who present stories of family violence or
abuse;
• People who live with disabled patients or with psychiatric
diseases.
